cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes an extension to the layer-wise relevance propagation framework for neural networks with local renormalization layers, which are commonly used in convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a specific method for extending the framework, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method is performed on image datasets, which could also suggest the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
